<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Hi Matt,<br>
<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; It seems that the right way to do it is the fallowing:<br>
<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; -mca btl openib,self -mca btl_openib_ib_pkey_val 33033<br>
<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; when the value is a decimal number of the pkey, in your case<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 0x8109 = 33033, and no need for btl_openib_ib_pkey_ix value.<br>
<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ex.<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; mpirun -np 2 -H witch2,witch3 -mca btl openib,self -mca<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; btl_openib_ib_pkey_val 32769 ./mpi_p1_4_1_2 -t lt<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; LT (2) (size min max avg) 1 3.511429 3.511429 3.511429<br>
<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; if it&#39;s not working check cat<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; /sys/class/infiniband/mthca0/ports/1/pkeys/* for pkeys ans SM,<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; maybe it&#39;s a setup.<br>
<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Pasha is currently checking this issue.<br>
<br>
 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Best regards,<br>
